This 3.9 acre parcel of land is zoned for multifamily housing and is located just off Centennial Boulevard in Warman, SK. The area is experiencing rapid development which will provide many amenities for future residents. These amenities include close proximity to a major grocer, home hardware store, and fast food restaurants.

Nestled in a picturesque bend of the South Saskatchewan River, less than five kilometers north of the city of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, RiverBend is a community with an innovative design which aspires to meet the basic principles of environmental and social sustainability. It is a complete community which includes acres of intriguing parks and green spaces, innovative public recreation facilities, opportunity for local businesses and community organizations and a variety of housing options meant to accommodate the dreams of a wide range of homebuyers.

CBRE is pleased to offer for sale a total of ± 5.05 acres for multifamily residential uses located in The Meadows, a 420 acre master-planned community, nestled in the Rosewood neighborhood of Saskatoon, SK. When completed, The Meadows will feature 2,200+ new homes and 65 acres of parks, ponds and pathways. Within the Meadows, lies the Meadows Market, a retail power centre with Costco, boutiques, restaurants, and many more  amenities. Overall, the site is well situated within Saskatoon and is a short 7 minute drive to the city center.

CBRE Limited is pleased to offer for sale this 0.4 acre multifamily development site in prestigious Varsity View. Zoned RM3 this site currently consists of five (5) houses and offers the opportunity for the construction of a low-rise, ~24-28 suite, apartment/condo building. The Development has the potential to be the standout rental property in the Varsity View neighborhood. CBRE Limited is pleased to offer for sale a total of ±86.61 acres for residential uses that includes 46 serviced lots in the northern portion of the Kensington neighbourhood in Saskatoon. The development lands, which comprise of ±86.61 acres, are designated for a mix of low and medium density residential uses and the 46 lots range in size from 28 feet to 54 feet.
